		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> 2 Towers Booster Draft at Quantum Cards<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=11045'>Patrick "Patrick M. S" Sullivan</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=11045&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 31, 2003</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Quantum Cards, Booster Draft (Towers format)<br />
Sunday, March 30th, 2003<br />
Pre-tourney JANK<br />
Favourite card-store with my favorite type of tournament. Who could ask for a sweeter way to spend a snowy Sunday afternoon? My gf would most certainly come up with plenty of answers to that question but since this dork is focused on spending his money needlessly on his addictive hobby, no one&#8217;s going to change his mind.<br />
I am coming over a 5-0 OPEN format tournament yesterday so my mood and confidence is pretty up. However, the last Booster Draft I participated in was in Vegas where I went 0-4. And I&#8217;m supposed to be King of Sealed Deck play! I&#8217;m gonna shoot somebody if I end up with that awful Elf/Discardable Unbound Hobbit Draft pack again. That thing was garbage. But just in case, I decided to bring a site path that would give me better odds than last time. He&#8217;s what I&#8217;m bringing:<br />
<br />
Tired Traveller (I just can&#8217;t see why I&#8217;d ever bring the other one)<br />
ATAR foil (one of the two I have left, by the way I&#8217;m selling one of them. Best offer is 60 U.S. and I&#8217;m throwing in a Smeagol T-shirt).<br />
Gullies (in case I get Legolas again)<br />
Derndingle (Not sure what my reasoning here is&#8230;, this is probably a really dumb choice, WHY WOULD I RUN?)<br />
Golden Hall (why not?)<br />
Ered Nimis (since last time I drafted a total of ZERO companions and allies, I think this site would help a wee bit)<br />
Deep of Helm (this site killed me every single game last time so I figure if I draw an Uruk-Hai draft pack, I can do the same to others (like mom always said&#8230;)<br />
Caves (fierce uruk-hai rocks the house)<br />
Hornburg Wall (I tried this last time and it didn&#8217;t work at all. But I am too chicken to play any of the other sites)<br />
Wizard&#8217;s Vale (Thou Shalt Not Choke)<br />
Palantir (I hate bidding high so I punish those that would do me harm by doing so).<br />
<br />
How&#8217;s that then? Looks to me like one messed up site path. If I get Aragorn, perhaps I&#8217;ll get lucky and draft up a RidderMark. Or maybe I&#8217;ll draft up a FOURTH (count em) ATAR foil. Who knows what the future holds? All I know is I am going to have a great time playing at Quantum Cards as I always do. <br />
<br />
So I swing by Tim Horton&#8217;s, grab a large coffee (I&#8217;ve got win that gosh darnit contest one of these days) and arrive at Quantum 5 minutes late. 9 players have shown up and we&#8217;re waiting for the 10th player who was supposed to come. He never shows up so we start the draft circle with 9. Who are the nine? Well they are (with sealed deck ratings)<br />
1. Jean-Luc Simard (1573, sprint: 1524)<br />
2. Me, Patrick Sullivan (1663 1st in the province!, sprint: 1540 2nd in province! OH NO!)<br />
3. Matthew (1500, 1st Booster Draft experience)<br />
4. Jonathan Verall (1637, sprint: 1562 1st in province! OH NO)<br />
5. John Bernatches (1593, sprint: 1500)<br />
6. Jonathan Keane (1585, sprint: 1516)<br />
7. Ariadne MacGee (1580, sprint: 1522)<br />
8. Alex MacGee (1516, sprint: 1500) who looked ravishing as always.<br />
9. Fred Coté (1554, sprint: 1500)<br />
<br />
So since I&#8217;ve already reserved my hotel room for Origins (along with Patrick and David Malboeuf, Mathieu Brochu and his GF, Hahn (winner of Arwen Championship at DecipherCon)), I have a vested interest in winning the 4-month sprint for best Sealed Deck player in my region. ESPECIALLY now that Day Two Premiere Series Origins and Day One Continentals will be the SAME day. So if ever I make day two Premiere and I haven&#8217;t won a TOC, I won&#8217;t be able to participate in the Continentals (which would suck). So I really need to either win this tournament or at the very least beat John Verall in order to lessen the differential between our ratings. And after this tournament, I only have one more change, a BOHD Sealed Deck on April 13th (if I get that Legolas starter again, I&#8217;m gonna burn the house down). <br />
<br />
So I am the ONLY Team Quantum member to show up. However, Team Alexis Nihon has four members representing. Verall, Keane, Ari and her brother Alex (who is also celebrating his birthday) are representing the local mall where most of them (2?!) work. This time they have spared no expense. They have printed out team logos and Special stickers adhered to their clothes. Also, of special note, they have each printed out a special site nine with a picture of the mall&#8217;s entrance and the game text reads: Shadow: If you cannot spot an Alexis Nihon employee, the ring-beared is corrupted. <br />
<br />
So after saying our hellos, I randomize the seating order for the booster draft and find myself between John Keane and matthew (it&#8217;s his first Booster draft so this is probably a good thing for me when he passes right to me). <br />
My draft pack consists of a brilliant mix of Uruk-Hai Site Control and a couple raiders and the fellowship is all over the map but mostly consisting of Ring-Bound Rangers. Good thing I brought the Tired Travellor himself.<br />
<br />
First booster pack I open contains the Answer to All Riddles as the rare. I can&#8217;t seem to avoid nailing this card, however this time it&#8217;s not foil so I pass it up and take something else.<br />
<br />
Second Booster pack (BOHD) contains nothing really extrodinary (Down from the Hills)<br />
However the third pack contains Grima Wormtougne which I take just in case.<br />
<br />
So I build up a 50 card deck (pretty big but I have drafted a ton of Dwarf conditions (including Ever my Heart Rises) that will cycle very very fast. I pick out my top 9 companions out of the 14 I drafted (I always draft companions not just for me but to negative draft my opponents packs). I will need to start Gimli for sure because of all my dwarf conditions and boosts and I&#8217;ll start a ranger of ithien for similar reasons. If someone starts the site one that gets gimli then I&#8217;ll use the Lady of Rohan instead of Gimli. In fact that would be  such a smart start that I decide to go second every opportunity I have. Oh by the way, the only site I drafted was East Wall of Rohan which I put in since I did not get Gimli (although I did get the White Wizard along with Down from the Hills).<br />
<br />
I decide I will be able to bid 5. Removing 3 with my RBR and 1 with my foil brace of coneys thus moving to Palantir Chamber with 1 burden (I like dat). <br />
<br />
So here we go:<br />
<br />
Round one<br />
Me (1663) vs John Keane (1585)<br />
John seems to have a new hair style. I hope it doesn&#8217;t throw me off my game&#61514;<br />
I bid five to his zero (or two I can&#8217;t recall) and let him go first because I&#8217;m hoping that someone is playing the site that gets Gimli. He isn&#8217;t. Darn. This game went VERY slowly. There was always a huge pause after I finished playing my minions and waiting for him to decide what to do. I think John looks at the situation and decides his maneuver, archery, assignment and skirmish moves all during the maneuver phase. Because once he&#8217;s made up his mind, the rest goes very quickly. But it gives the appearance of a 5 minute Maneuver phase each time. Anyway his shadow was doing a bang-up job of slowing down my fellowship so I had to stop at the site 6 sanctuary when he was already at site 7. So he moves to 8 and I play two minions. I had done quite a number on his fellowship at my Deep of Helm (good site choice in the end) and my two minions at site 8 held their own and made it to the regroup phase. At this point, John had a bit of a dilemna, either he could double move and go for the full win or stop and most likely get a timed win (unless I double move and then I would get the timed win). I try to help him out and tell him if he wants to stop, he just has to not play any minions on me and then he would get to his fellowship phase real quick and could single move to nine. However, he makes the ethical decision to move again to try to end the game. I drew up 6 minions and threw them down and he conceeds. Timed games really suck sometimes...<br />
FW +3/3<br />
Good: Playing against John is always a pleasure. Very relaxed matches and we always have a good time.	<br />
Bad: Those gosh darnit 5 minute maneuver phases were the reason our game almost went to time. <br />
Ugly: Me pulling up a perfect site 9 hand. Poor John. That would have been really cool if he had won at site 9 by double moving. That would have been sweet justice for us both.<br />
<br />
Verall had mentionned that he would give the winner of that first game a big kiss and I was the lucky recipient. So I get a big wet one on the cheek and I&#8217;m hoping it wasn&#8217;t the kiss of death because of my next pairing...<br />
<br />
Round Two<br />
Me (1663) vs Jonathan Verall (1637)<br />
I don&#8217;t think a single tournament hasn&#8217;t gone by where my match up against Verall was the one to watch. It&#8217;s always a real nail-biter and is usually the catalyst of which one of us gets the chance to go undefeated and win the tournament. I think since the beginning of time, we have taken turns in winning matches. We both know it&#8217;s my turn to win this time because of his fellowship win against me at the BOHD pre-release (where he forgot at 3 or 4 sites that his wargs were fierce but STILL managed to beat my weak elves). Anyway he&#8217;s a scholar and a gentlemen and to all you young ladies out there, he&#8217;s newly single! Hot cakes like these don&#8217;t stay on the display shelf for long. Anyway enough with the &#8216;Three&#8217;s Company&#8217; banter as Andrew Howard likes to call it. On to the game. So I bid 5 to his zero and let him go first. Same reasoning as the first game and I really want my Deep of Helm to come out because it did a number on Verall&#8217;s teammate that I vanquished earlier on. Jonathan is having a rough time compared to my fellowship because I got pretty well set up early. I&#8217;m right behind him and he moves to site 4 and faces moderate opposition. Jonathan is a no-guts-no-glory kind of guy most of the time and this time he sticks to it and doubles to my deep of helm. OOPS. I manage to get out a total of 7 minions to his 7 companions. YAY Frodo is fighting. Frodo is power 4 (3 base plus one for the Ruling Ring (Jonathan hates burdens). So I need to 8 strength to win the game but two of the 7 minions are 6 strength and I have ZERO pumps in my hand. However on the table is a Wrath of Harad (nice pull) which would pump my little Southron Archer (bad pull) from 6 to 8. That takes care of that strength six minion. What about the other one? It&#8217;s a strength six Uruk Beseiger. However, There is an Uruk Rear Guard on the table with 4 vitality that can exert to add 1 strength to an uruk-hai at a battleground. Last time I checked, Deep of Helm was not only a plains but a battleground as well. Jonathan looks at the various ways he can attempt to hit my Uruk Rear Guard for 2 bringing my pump capability to +1 instead of  +3. He managed to assign it to Eowyn (or Theoden) with a horsey which exerts my Guard once. But he then loses the skimish allowing me to pump the beseiger twice, overwhelming Frodo. Game, set, match.<br />
FW +3 / 6<br />
Good: Easily my favorite opponent at Quantum Cards (or in the world, for that matter). We allowed each other take backs and had a fun time. Too bad it didn&#8217;t work out for Verall but MAN, did I ever need the win.<br />
Bad: Double moving to Deep of Helm when I&#8217;m ready for him.<br />
Ugly: Next time it&#8217;s my turn to lose....<br />
<br />
Round Three<br />
Me (1663) vs Jean-Luc simard (1573)<br />
Jean-Luc is fresh back from a trip to Decipher headquarters where he experienced a weekend of playtesting Ents of Fanghorn. What an amazing experience that must have been. And I don&#8217;t doubt for a second that it has made him a dangerous booster draft opponent since he knows the cards so well. I bid five to his 2 and let him start. He is playing RidderMark and I thus helped him tremendously. I decide at that moment that I should really be starting to ensure that my opponent doesn&#8217;t get their Aragorn (which I don&#8217;t have). I get my fellowship set up pretty well (8 companions out at site 3) but his gets set up better. He doubles twice and is at site 5 before I know it. When I try to move to 4, I hit a world of hurt. He plays 4 raiders, all of which opportunize on a fellowship of 6 companions or greater. The first one discards companions of HIS choice if I don&#8217;t assign him to the ring-bearer. Since I didn&#8217;t draft one gosh darnit stealth, I can&#8217;t let that happen (his minions is 14 strength). So he discards my Gondorian Ranger and Eowyn (I think). I know have 6 companions left so he uses the other southron that does the same thing but I get to pick who is discarded. Thank God I get to reshuffle my discard pile back into my draw deck later on. Anyway he has effectively slowed my fellowship to a crawl. That and to make matters worse, my Ever My Heart Rises has stacked 5 minions that I desperately need and can now never get back again. So he takes a breather at site 6 and then moves to nine with very little opposition. <br />
FL +1/ 7<br />
Good: Not much really. It was a really dull game cuz both my shadow and my fellowship got really screwed<br />
Bad: 5 minions on Ever My Heart Rises<br />
Ugly: I forgot to use my Site 4 ally as a speedbump and lost another companion for no reason.<br />
<br />
Round Four<br />
Me (1663) vs Fred Coté (1554)<br />
I&#8217;m so happy that my final round is against a real nice guy. Fred is the local champion of league play and is unstoppable with his Uruk Archery deck (which inspired me to try one someday). Fred and I smiled the whole game and had real fun. I bid 5 to his zero (I think) and elect to go first (let&#8217;s see how this works). I can see by the pain on his face that he was really looking forward to getting Riddermark out so I realize I should have been doing this all day since everyone drafted Aragorn except me I think. At site 3, in this game, I have not 8 but NINE companions on the table and I,m in the lead!. Hurray for everything. I stopped at site 4 and Fred decides to double move past me into the Deep of Helm since he realizes he won&#8217;t beat my fellowship. The problem is, his fellowship consists of 3 companions INCLUDING Frodo. OOPS. I throw down a barrage of minions and down goes Frodo.<br />
FW +3/10<br />
Good: Fred is a great opponent and we never get to play each other (as I don&#8217;t come to league nights and he usually doesn&#8217;t come to weekend tourneys because of work)<br />
Bad: I should have been going first all day now that I see the fruits of Ever My Heart Rises (I always stacked two companions to fetch)<br />
Ugly: 3 companions doubling to Deep of Helm. OUCH.<br />
<br />
So that&#8217;s it. In the last round, Jean-Luc was paired up against Verall. If  the latter had won, I think I would have won the tournament because I had an excellent strength of schedule but alas he too loses and Jean-Luc wins the tournament going undefeated. I come in second place and win a booster. I open it up and get the Company of Haradrim. YUCK. SO I buy an Eowyn starter to practice up for the sealed deck coming up and also purchase my first box of Dragon Shield plastics which I hear are the best. Purple. Pretty....<br />
<br />
Props:<br />
Ari for writing notes on my TR scribble sheet where I write game details. I made sure to include her comments in my TR although I interpreted it my way &#61514;<br />
Verall for his no-guts-no-glory policy<br />
Keane for doing the right thing to do by double moving to end the game before time ran out.<br />
Fred Cote for coming to a Sunday tournament for once.<br />
John Bernatchez for getting the notes perfectly right on the Isengard theme music from Fellowship.<br />
Matthew for coming to his first booster draft<br />
Alex for coming out to a tournament (must come more often me-boy)<br />
Jill for running the best card shop EVER and for running the store alone that day (there was a ton of people)<br />
<br />
Slops:<br />
Me for calling Jill, &#8216;Kathy&#8217;. Dang. <br />
My coffee at Tim Horton&#8217;s was Yet another loser. Darn.<br />
Team Alexis Nihon for scrubbing out big time. Haha. They kept getting matched up against each other. It was so funny.<br />
Me for getting another ATAR in a booster pack. I&#8217;m sick of that card. Decipher should really consider making all future copies of Frodo, the Ring and all sites COMMON because you can&#8217;t do jack with double copies....<br />
<br />
Next weekend, Open Format at Quantum Cards. Can&#8217;t wait. <br />
<br />
Hope you liked the TR.... <br />
